KRYL-1041 — EDGE Semantic Layer Contract & Enforcement Framework

Type: Architecture Work Order / RFC
Status: Architecture Review Ready
Classification: [SYS] Core Operating Constraint
Version Impact: v3.10.0 candidate after implementation
Current Baseline: f35f998
Current Version: v3.9.0
Implementation Status: Deferred pending architecture approval

Decision Request

Approve:

EDGE Semantic Layer Contract and authorize implementation planning under E1–E7 enforcement constraints.

Objective

Introduce EDGE as a first-class semantic layer that identifies evidence-backed structural asymmetries while preventing:

unsupported inference
forward prediction
execution leakage
certainty inflation

EDGE describes system structure.

EDGE does not produce actions.

Architecture Placement
Signal
  ↓
Identity Kernel
  ↓
CanonicalEvent
  ↓
Evidence Layer
  ↓
EDGE Semantic Layer
  ↓
Structural Confirmation
  ↓
Projection / Rendering
Doctrine Contract
EDGE MAY
classify evidence-backed structural relationships
expose structural asymmetries
preserve uncertainty states
attach provenance
provide semantic context
EDGE MUST NOT
predict outcomes
generate recommendations
create execution instructions
calculate returns
create alpha signals
bypass Evidence Layer
Enforcement Invariants
E1 — Evidence Required

Failure:

EDGE_WITHOUT_EVIDENCE

Requirement:

Every EDGE classification requires ≥1 evidence reference.

E2 — Provenance Required

Failure:

EDGE_UNTRACEABLE

Requirement:

Every EDGE classification requires:

source
timestamp
lineage
E3 — Execution Boundary

Failure:

EDGE_EXECUTION_BOUNDARY_BREACH

EDGE payload cannot contain:

buy
sell
order
position
allocate
target_price
recommendation
E4 — Unknown Preservation

Failure:

EDGE_FALSE_CERTAINTY

Supported states:

EDGE_UNKNOWN
EDGE_ABSENT
EDGE_OBSERVED
EDGE_CONTESTED
EDGE_STALE

Unknown cannot collapse into classification.

E5 — Layer Direction

Failure:

EDGE_LAYER_INVERSION

Allowed:

Evidence → EDGE
Identity → EDGE
CanonicalEvent → EDGE

Forbidden:

EDGE → Evidence Creation
EDGE → Recommendation
EDGE → Execution
E6 — Semantic Escalation Prevention

Failure:

EDGE_SEMANTIC_ESCALATION

Requirement:

EDGE confidence cannot exceed evidence-supported confidence.

E7 — Evidence Boundary Preservation

Failure:

EDGE_FORWARD_INFERENCE

Requirement:

EDGE may derive classifications from evidence-backed relationships but may not introduce unsupported facts, causal claims, or future-state assertions.

